                320 kbps | MP3 | unmixed | 2014 | 03:58:59 | 547 Mb


However, since the series inception there has always been one glaring omission to the collection - So we thought it was time we took inspiration from our most famous, enigmatic and influential super club and pieced together an incredible journey depicting the biggest dance music genre that's ever lived. LET THERE BE HOUSE! This is Anthems House. Ministry of Sound have been at the forefront of dance music culture for well over 20 years, so who better to bring you this incredible 3CD collection detailing the history of house from its beginnings in Chicago in the mid 1980s right up to the present day. WHeller, Basement Jaxx, Sandy B, Modjo and Danny Tenaglia. After all the music really does sounds better with you. Ministry of Sound presents - Anthems House.
